52 West 132nd Street, south side, east of Lenox Avenue. This is a 2½-story frame house with a stucco front.

1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York. Negative No. 320.

52-74 West 132nd Street, south side, east of Lenox Ave. The Bethel African Methodist Episcopal Church is in the centre. The house on each side of the church is a frame with a stucco front.

August 1, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

62-52 West 132nd Street, south side, east of Lenox Ave.
In the centre is the Bethel African Methodist Episcopal Church; the two houses flanking the church are frame with stucco facings.

August 1, 1932.

P.L. Sperr.

63 West 132nd Street, north side, east of Lenox Avenue. This is a two-story frame house.

1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.

70-72 West 132nd Street, south side, east of Lenox Avenue. Both are three-story frame houses, No. 70 with a wooden and No. 72 with a stucco front.

1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York

Two frame houses, 72-70 West 132nd Street, the former with a stucco front, south side, east of Lenox Ave.
